task.summary: Sharded streams seem to work now (Identifier 1 is always used. Need to expand it to handle more than one).
Adds foreman gem and Procfile for starting up redis, signalling server, api, web
Updates callbacks and updates redis callback to add state information about peerconnections and streams.
Adds onSubscribe callback. Cleans up strings.
Adds PathedPcDetails and StandardPcDetails. Updates code sections to use appropriate version. Cleans up unused code. Adds logic to clean up registry PeerConnections.
Adds intermediate registryId redis key. Adds partial disconnection logic.
Adds logging ids. Updates redis keys. Removes two unused callbacks.
Updates logging. Moves init logic into method that can be called again. Moves PeerConnection.Observer logic out of the actor and into method that returns new on every call.

Removes automatic publishing to all registry nodes at start. Will now set up as needed. Re-initializes structures on disconnect to fix publishing multiple times with same identifier without having to restart server. Sets redis app to use publisher region in proxy mode. Moves observers into separate files.
Fixes missed clean up item in redis. Removes unused code.
Changes the registry to be a supervisor that manages creation/deletion of RegistryEntries. Creates RegistryEntry to contain Registry PeerConnections.
Cleans up unused code. Updates RedisCallback.
Fixes issue where Subscriber shard was never handling messages. Fixes Re-streaming to new subscriber.
Removes old code. Adds Signal class with messages. Adds publisher prefix to publisher messages.
Adds publisher and subscriber with shared signal handler.
Adds publisher and subscriber prefix to respective messages. Adds warning message for unhandled messages.
Adds onIceConnectionChange to subscriber callback. Sends PoisonPill message to subscriber on disconnect.
Adds PublisherSubscriber factory. Changes Publisher and Subscriber constructors to take an identifier.
Removes unused code sections. Cleans up formatting

Removes hard-coded identifiers. Introduces concept of one-time use, one purpose identifiers. Any number of publishers and subscribers can be created from a client. Adds a PublisherSubscriberFactory so that a single SignalHandler can be shared. Adds an IdentifierResolver so that the redis gateway can just look up the correct origin independently.
Adds TODO about what to do when Publisher disconnection happens.

Adds Docker, Vagrant, linux support! Updates hard-coded localhost references for Vagrant multi-machine configuration Updates webrtc java libs. Updates overridden method definitions. Google appears to have fixed remote streams being relayed back so custom jni methods can be removed. See (https://code.google.com/p/webrtc/issues/detail?id=383) Updates media packer with additional required webrtc libraries. WebRTC was crashing on native initialization because it could not initialize the VoiceEngine. Removes vagrant dotfiles.
